],"conformsTo":"http://mlcommons.org/croissant/1.1","name":"SWE-rebench","description":"\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\tDataset Summary\n\t\n\nSWE-rebench is a large-scale dataset designed to support the training and evaluation of LLM-based software engineering (SWE) agents. It is built using a fully automated pipeline that continuously extracts real-world GitHub tasks at scale. The dataset includes over 21,000 issue–pull request pairs from 6,000+ Python repositories, each validated for correctness through environment setup and test execution.\n\nSWE-rebench expands on the methodology introduced in SWE-bench… See the full description on the dataset page: https://huggingface.co/datasets/nebius/SWE-rebench.","alternateName":["nebius/SWE-rebench"],"creator":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Nebius","url":"https://huggingface.co/nebius"},"keywords":["10K - 100K","parquet","Text","Datasets","Dask","Croissant","Polars","🇺🇸 Region: US"],"url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/nebius/SWE-rebench"}